This paper deals with face image analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves constructing a unified tensor model and using tensor completion methods, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of cascaded-regression-based methods for fitting the model, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
